{"title_page": "Living On Video (1986 album)", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|text= the [[Living On Video (album)|1983 debut album]] by Trans-X}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Living On Video\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Trans-X]]\n| cover        = Living On Video album.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = 1986\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = Ultrasound Studios, [[Montreal]]\n| genre        = {{hlist|[[Synth-pop]]|[[new wave]]}}\n| length       = 46:07 (Canadian version)<br>41:10 (US version)\n| label        = {{hlist|Image|[[Atco Records|ATCO]]}}\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[Living On Video (album)|Living On Video]]\n| prev_year    = 1983\n| next_title   = On My Own\n| next_year    = 1988\n}}\n\n'''''Living On Video''''' is the second album by Canadian [[synth-pop]] band [[Trans-X]], released in 1986 in Canada by Image Records, a sublabel of [[Unidisc Music#Sublabels|Matra Records]], in the US by [[Atco Records|ATCO Records]] and it was also released in some countries in Europe. This album should not be confused with the band's [[Living On Video (album)|1983 album of the same name]], which also has the same cover art.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Trans-X-Living-On-Video/master/48928|title=Trans-X - Living On Video|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> This album has 9 tracks and some different tracks. More confusing is that different versions of the album were released in Canada and the US with the same track listing, but with different track durations.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Trans-X-Living-On-Video/release/2002498|title=Trans-X - Living On Video|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>    \n\nThe most notable difference between the two album versions is the different versions of \"[[Living on Video]]\". The Canadian version is a re-recorded version, produced by Richard Buck in 1986, whereas the US version is a 1985 remix, produced by Daniel Barnier.<ref name=\":0\" /> The album features 3 songs that were on the 1983 album: \"Living on Video\", \"3-D Monkey\" and \"Message on the Radio\". However, these songs are all different versions.    \n\nThere were three singles from the album. The 1985 remix of \"Living on Video\" peaked at number 61 on the [[Billboard Hot 100]] in June 1986.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/1986-06-21|title=The Hot 100 Chart|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> The other two singles, released in 1986, were \"Ich Liebe Dich (I Love You)\" and \"Monkey Dance\", neither of which charted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bac-lac.on.worldcat.org/oclc/1006664355?lang=en&new=-8586156897791600000|title=Item Details Page for Ich liebe dich (I love you)|website=bac-lac.on.worldcat.org|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bac-lac.on.worldcat.org/oclc/1006664231|title=Item Details Page for Monkey dance ; Hey boy get it right|website=bac-lac.on.worldcat.org|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>    \n\nThe majority of the tracks on this album (specifically the Canadian version), along with those on the 1983 album, were included on the [[Living On Video (album)#1993 CD Reissue|1993 CD release]].        \n\n== Track listing ==\n\n=== Canadian version ===\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Side A\n| title3 = 3-D Dance\n| extra4 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| writer4 = Denis Toupin, Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| title4 = Monkey Dance\n| length3 = 5:40\n| extra3 = Daniel Bernier\n| writer3 = Daniel Bernier, Dominique Nicodemo, Pascal Languirand\n| note3 = Remix\n| length2 = 3:31\n| extra_column = '''Producer(s)'''\n| extra2 = Pascal Languirand, Ren\u00e9 Grignon\n| writer2 = Pascal Languirand, Ren\u00e9 Grignon\n| title2 = Eyes of Desire\n| length1 = 7:02\n| extra1 = Richard Buck\n| writer1 = Pascal Languirand\n| note1 = 1986 Re-Recording\n| title1 = [[Living on Video]]\n| length4 = 5:50\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Side B\n| extra7 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| extra9 = Daniel Bernier\n| writer9 = Pascal Languirand\n| note9 = Remix\n| title9 = Message on the Radio\n| length8 = 3:34\n| extra8 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| writer8 = Denis Toupin, Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand, Paule Morin\n| title8 = Something's in the Air\n| length7 = 5:26\n| writer7 = Denis Toupin, Frederic Weber, Jocelyn Therrien, Pascal Languirand, Paule Morin, Sylvie Daviau\n| extra_column = '''Producer(s)'''\n| title7 = Ich Liebe Dich (I Love You)\n| length6 = 4:30\n| extra6 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| writer6 = Denis Toupin, Frederic Weber, Norman Kerr, Pascal Languirand, Paule Morin\n| title6 = Ghost\n| length5 = 5:08\n| extra5 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| writer5 = Denis Toupin, Frederic Weber, Jocelyn Therrien, Pascal Languirand, Paule Morin, Sylvie Daviau\n| title5 = Through the Eyes of the Nineties\n| length9 = 5:26\n}}\n\n=== US version ===\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Side A\n| extra_column = '''Producer(s)'''\n| title1 = [[Living on Video]]\n| note1 = 1985 Remix\n| extra1 = Daniel Bernier\n| length1 = 5:30\n| title2 = Eyes of Desire\n| length2 = 3:30\n| title3 = 3-D Dance\n| note3 = Remix\n| length3 = 5:42\n| title4 = Monkey Dance\n| length4 = 5:42\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Side B\n| extra_column = '''Producer(s)'''\n| title5 = Through the Eyes of the Nineties\n| note5 = Remix\n| length5 = 3:50\n| title6 = Ghost\n| note6 = US Remix\n| length6 = 3:55\n| title7 = Ich Liebe Dich (I Love You)\n| note7 = Remix\n| length7 = 4:07\n| title8 = Something's in the Air\n| length8 = 3:32\n| title9 = Message on the Radio\n| note9 = Remix\n| length9 = 5:22\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1986 albums]]\n[[Category:Trans-X albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|text= the [[Living On Video (album)|1983 debut album]] by Trans-X}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Living On Video\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Trans-X]]\n| cover        = Living On Video album.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = 1986\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = Ultrasound Studios, [[Montreal]]\n| genre        = {{hlist|[[Synth-pop]]|[[new wave]]}}\n| length       = 46:07 (Canadian version)<br>41:10 (US version)\n| label        = {{hlist|Image|[[Atco Records|ATCO]]}}\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[Living On Video (album)|Living On Video]]\n| prev_year    = 1983\n| next_title   = On My Own\n| next_year    = 1988\n}}\n\n'''''Living On Video''''' is the second album by Canadian synth-pop band Trans-X, released in 1986 in Canada by Image Records, a sublabel of [[Unidisc Music#Sublabels|Matra Records]], in the US by [[Atco Records|ATCO Records]] and it was also released in Europe. This album should not be confused with the band's [[Living On Video (album)|1983 album of the same name]], which also has the same cover art.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Trans-X-Living-On-Video/master/48928|title=Trans-X - Living On Video|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> This album has 9 tracks and some different tracks. More confusing is that different versions of the album were released in Canada and the US with the same track listing, but with different track durations.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Trans-X-Living-On-Video/release/2002498|title=Trans-X - Living On Video|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>    \n\nThe most notable difference between the two album versions is the different versions of \"[[Living on Video]]\". The Canadian version is a re-recorded version, produced by Richard Buck in 1986, whereas the US version is a 1985 remix, produced by Daniel Barnier.<ref name=\":0\" /> The album features 3 songs that were on the 1983 album: \"Living on Video\", \"3-D Monkey\" and \"Message on the Radio\". However, these songs are all different versions.    \n\nThere were three singles from the album. The 1985 remix of \"Living on Video\" peaked at number 61 on the [[Billboard Hot 100]] in June 1986.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/1986-06-21|title=The Hot 100 Chart|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> The other two singles, released in 1986, were \"Ich Liebe Dich (I Love You)\" and \"Monkey Dance\", neither of which charted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bac-lac.on.worldcat.org/oclc/1006664355?lang=en&new=-8586156897791600000|title=Item Details Page for Ich liebe dich (I love you)|website=bac-lac.on.worldcat.org|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bac-lac.on.worldcat.org/oclc/1006664231|title=Item Details Page for Monkey dance ; Hey boy get it right|website=bac-lac.on.worldcat.org|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>    \n\nThe majority of the tracks on this album (specifically the Canadian version), along with those on the 1983 album, were included on the [[Living On Video (album)#1993 CD Reissue|1993 CD release]].        \n\n== Track listing ==\n\n=== Canadian version ===\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Side A\n| title3 = 3-D Dance\n| extra4 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| writer4 = Denis Toupin, Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| title4 = Monkey Dance\n| length3 = 5:40\n| extra3 = Daniel Bernier\n| writer3 = Daniel Bernier, Dominique Nicodemo, Pascal Languirand\n| note3 = Remix\n| length2 = 3:31\n| extra_column = '''Producer(s)'''\n| extra2 = Pascal Languirand, Ren\u00e9 Grignon\n| writer2 = Pascal Languirand, Ren\u00e9 Grignon\n| title2 = Eyes of Desire\n| length1 = 7:02\n| extra1 = Richard Buck\n| writer1 = Pascal Languirand\n| note1 = 1986 Re-Recording\n| title1 = [[Living on Video]]\n| length4 = 5:50\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Side B\n| extra7 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| extra9 = Daniel Bernier\n| writer9 = Pascal Languirand\n| note9 = Remix\n| title9 = Message on the Radio\n| length8 = 3:34\n| extra8 = Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand\n| writer8 = Denis Toupin, Frederic Weber, Pascal Languirand, Pa