{"title_page": "In Your Eyes (Robin Schulz song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = In Your Eyes\n| cover      = Robin Schulz - In Your Eyes.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Robin Schulz]] featuring [[Alida]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{Start date|2020|01|10|df=yes}}\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=34}}\n| label      = [[Warner Music Group|Warner Germany]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Robin Schulz]]\n* [[Alida|Alida Garpestad Peck]]\n* Daniel Deimann\n* Junkx\n| producer   =\n* Robin Schulz\n* Erik Smaaland\n* Gaute Orm\u00e5sen\n* Kristoffer T\u00f8mmerbakke\n| chronology = [[Robin Schulz]]\n| prev_title = [[Rather Be Alone (Robin Schulz, Nick Martin and Sam Martin song)|Rather Be Alone]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|mDLiAs5k1oI|\"In Your Eyes\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''In Your Eyes'''\" is a song by German producer [[Robin Schulz]], featuring vocals from Norwegian singer [[Alida]]. It was released by [[Warner Music Group|Warner Music Group Germany]] to [[Music download|digital download]] and [[Media streaming|streaming]] formats on 10 January 2020. The song was written by Schulz, [[Alida|Alida Garpestad Peck]], Daniel Deimann & Dennis \"Junkx\" Bierbrodt. Production was handled by [[Robin Schulz]], Erik Smaaland, Gaute Orm\u00e5sen & Kristoffer T\u00f8mmerbakke\n\n== Charts ==\n<!-- Do NOT add digital component charts when the main country's chart is ALREADY listed. They WILL be removed. See [[WP:CHARTMATH]]. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|3|artist=Robin Schulz|song=In Your Eyes|rowheader=true|accessdate=2 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|26|artist=Robin Schulz|song=In Your Eyes